@page "/terms"
@attribute [Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization.AllowAnonymous]
@layout GoatLab.Client.Layout.LandingLayout
@inject LegalSettingsService Legal

<PageTitle>Terms of Service — GoatLab</PageTitle>

<section class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
        @if (_settings is null || !_settings.Approved)
        {
            <MudAlert Severity="Severity.Warning" Class="mb-6">
                <strong>Draft, not legal advice.</strong> This document is a starting-point draft pending
                attorney review. Bracketed items <code>[LIKE THIS]</code> are placeholders for the lawyer
                to finalize. Do not rely on these terms for any binding purpose until the version
                without bracketed placeholders is published here.
            </MudAlert>
        }

        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="effective">Last updated: @DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("MMMM yyyy")</p>

        <h2>1. About these Terms</h2>
        <p>
            These Terms of Service (<strong>"Terms"</strong>) are a binding agreement between you
            (<strong>"you"</strong>, <strong>"your"</strong>, <strong>"Customer"</strong>) and
            <strong>@LegalSettingsService.Or(_settings?.EntityName, "LEGAL ENTITY NAME")</strong>,
            a @LegalSettingsService.Or(_settings?.State, "STATE") @LegalSettingsService.Or(_settings?.EntityType, "LLC / corporation / sole proprietor")
            with its principal place of business at <strong>@LegalSettingsService.Or(_settings?.BusinessAddress, "BUSINESS ADDRESS")</strong>
            (<strong>"GoatLab"</strong>, <strong>"we"</strong>, <strong>"us"</strong>,
            <strong>"our"</strong>). They govern your access to and use of the GoatLab software
            service, the website at https://goatlab.app, mobile and PWA clients, APIs, and all
            related products (collectively, the <strong>"Service"</strong>).
        </p>
        <p>
            By creating an account, accessing, or using the Service, you confirm that you have read,
            understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms and our
            <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>, which is incorporated by reference. If you do not
            agree, do not use the Service.
        </p>
        <p>
            If you are accepting these Terms on behalf of a business, organization, or other legal
            entity, you represent that you have authority to bind that entity, and "you" refers to
            that entity.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Eligibility</h2>
        <p>
            You may use the Service only if you are at least <strong>16 years old</strong> and
            legally able to form a binding contract under the laws of your jurisdiction. We do not
            knowingly collect data from individuals under 16 and do not intend the Service for use
            by minors. If you become aware that a minor has provided us data, contact us at
            <strong>@LegalSettingsService.Or(_settings?.ContactEmail, "CONTACT EMAIL")</strong> so we can delete it.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Description of the Service</h2>
        <p>
            GoatLab is a software-as-a-service platform for goat farm management. The Service allows
            you to record and analyze data about your animals (including medical records, breeding
            history, milk production, weights, sales, and finances), upload photos and documents,
            generate reports, share public listings of animals you offer for sale, receive automated
            alerts and reminders, and collaborate with team members.
        </p>
        <p>
            The Service is provided "as is" and is updated frequently. Features, pricing, plan tiers,
            and limits may change at our discretion, with reasonable notice for material changes
            affecting paid plans.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Accounts and Tenants</h2>
        <h3>4.1. Account creation</h3>
        <p>
            To use most features you must create an individual user account by providing a valid
            email address and password. You may also be invited to join an existing
            <strong>Tenant</strong> (a "Farm") created by another user.
        </p>
        <h3>4.2. Tenant ownership</h3>
        <p>
            Each Farm is created by a user who becomes its <strong>Owner</strong>. The Owner controls
            billing, subscription, team membership, public-page visibility, and may delete the Farm.
            Members and Viewers have reduced permissions as described in the Service.
        </p>
        <h3>4.3. Account security</h3>
        <p>
            You are responsible for safeguarding your credentials, enabling two-factor authentication
            where offered, and for all activity occurring under your account. Notify us immediately
            at <strong>@LegalSettingsService.Or(_settings?.ContactEmail, "CONTACT EMAIL")</strong> if you suspect unauthorized access.
        </p>
        <h3>4.4. One human per account</h3>
        <p>
            Each individual user account must be used by a single natural person. Sharing account
            credentials is prohibited and may result in suspension.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Subscriptions, Trials, and Billing</h2>
        <h3>5.1. Plans</h3>
        <p>
            We offer multiple subscription tiers (currently Homestead [free], Farm, and Dairy).
            Tier-specific features, animal limits, and team-member limits are displayed on the
            pricing page and in the application. We may add, remove, rename, or re-price tiers at
            our discretion with at least <strong>30 days'</strong> notice for changes affecting
            active paid subscriptions.
        </p>
        <h3>5.2. Free trials</h3>
        <p>
            New paid subscriptions may include a free trial period (currently 14 days on Farm and
            Dairy). At the end of the trial, your subscription will automatically convert to paid
            and your payment method will be charged the then-current price for that tier,
            <strong>unless you cancel before the trial ends</strong>. We may modify trial duration
            or eligibility at any time.
        </p>
        <h3>5.3. Payment</h3>
        <p>
            Paid subscriptions are billed through <strong>Stripe, Inc.</strong>
            (<strong>"Stripe"</strong>). By providing a payment method, you authorize us (via Stripe)
